<% content_for :title, "Terms | DevDeBizz" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Review the DevDeBizz terms of service covering website use, subscriptions, projects, and client responsibilities." %>

<%= render "page_header",
  eyebrow: "Terms",
  title_html: 'Terms of <span class="home-display-accent">Service</span>'.html_safe,
  subtitle: "Rules, guidelines, and terms for browsing and utilizing the DevDeBizz website." %>

<section class="py-20">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-2 md:px-0">
    <div class="home-glass home-card-3d rounded-[32px] p-8 md:p-12 space-y-8 text-[#081849]/80 leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#081849] mb-3">1. Website Scope</h2>
        <p>The content on this website is provided for general business information about DevDeBizz and its website architecture services.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#081849] mb-3">2. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All branding, custom copy, design assets, and interactive materials on this website remain the property of DevDeBizz unless otherwise agreed in writing.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#081849] mb-3">3. Contractual Relationship</h2>
        <p>Use of this site does not create a formal developer-client relationship. A partnership is only established once both parties have signed a separate, customized project scope agreement.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#081849] mb-3">4. Contact Details</h2>
        <p>For questions regarding our terms, services, or licensing agreements, please reach out directly via: <%= link_to contact_email, "mailto:#{contact_email}", class: "font-semibold underline text-[#213885]" %>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
